ates their significance, discusses Philippi's methods of encountering the "strangeness" of Japan, and comments astutely on aspects of the encounter of East and West.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aShintovPrayers and devotions. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / Japanese.2bisacsh  aAkitsu-Kami.  aGoddesses.  aHeavenly Sins.  aHirano no maturi.  aHonji Suijaku.  aImperial Plantations.  aIndividual Norito.  aKasuga maturi.  aMidu-ho no kuni.  aNakatomi.  aPriestesses.  aSovereign.  aanthropos.  acorpus Christianum.  adoctrine.  aheavenly.  aimperium.  aishin.  akotodama.  amassively.  amawosu.  amuro.  anegi.  asacerdotium.  asemmyō.  astudium.  auti-bito.  ayama-no-kuti.1 aKitagawa, Joseph M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKitagawa, Joseph Mitsuo.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Gap Yearsz978311078423740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691214528zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691214528423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691214528/original  a978-3-11-044249-6  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999c1927d1999  a978-3-11-078423-7  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Gap Years  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK